Milestone 1: Data Pipeline and Project Foundation

Main objective
Build a reliable and reusable data pipeline so the dog breed classification project is runnable end-to-end before model training.

Project structural design (how we organized the system)
We used a modular structure so each part of the pipeline has one clear responsibility:

1) Data splitting and folder setup
- File: src/scripts/download_and_split.py
- Role: takes raw breed folders from Images/ and creates data/train, data/val, and data/test.
- Design reason: guarantees a standard dataset layout for every team member and every experiment.

2) Dataset abstraction
- File: src/dataset.py
- Role: defines StanfordDogsDataset to read image paths, map breed folders to label indices, and load images as RGB tensors.
- Includes image validation using PIL verify() to skip corrupted/unreadable files.
- Design reason: keeps dataset logic centralized and robust.

3) Preprocessing and augmentation
- File: src/transforms.py
- Role: defines split-specific transforms:
  - train: resize, random crop, horizontal flip, color jitter, rotation, normalize
  - val/test: deterministic resize + center crop + normalize
- Uses ImageNet mean/std to match pretrained CNN expectations.
- Design reason: improves generalization while keeping evaluation consistent.

4) DataLoader factory and balancing
- File: src/data_loader.py
- Role: builds DataLoader objects for train/val/test and supports optional WeightedRandomSampler for class imbalance.
- Also provides class distribution summary helpers.
- Design reason: one interface for loading data in training, evaluation, and debugging scripts.

5) Pipeline verification script
- File: src/verify_pipeline.py
- Role: performs sanity checks before training:
  - verifies tensor and label shapes
  - checks label-to-class mapping
  - prints class distribution stats
  - saves sample image grid to outputs/
- Design reason: catches data and preprocessing errors early, before expensive training runs.

Implementation process (what was done in Milestone 1)
- Inspected the raw dog image dataset and confirmed breed folder naming format.
- Built deterministic train/val/test split generation with configurable ratios and seed.
- Implemented dataset loading with corruption filtering and clean class-index mapping.
- Implemented preprocessing pipelines aligned with transfer learning best practices.
- Implemented DataLoader creation for all splits with optional class rebalancing.
- Added end-to-end verification script to confirm the pipeline is stable and runnable.

How this is easier for users/teammates to understand
- Clear separation of responsibilities: split -> dataset -> transforms -> loader -> verification.
- One command to build splits and one command to verify the full pipeline.
- Consistent data structure across environments (local machine and Colab).
- Friendly printed checks (shape, labels, distribution) make debugging straightforward.

